{
  "texts": [
    "In the encoder, we use six convolutional layers with a stride of two so that each layer halves the spatial dimension.",
    "The spatial reduction allows the subsequent layers to capture information at larger scales in the input flow data, which also has similarities to the multiple scales of the studied chaotic flow and can help to represent it.",
    "The number of filters in each layer progressively increases to preserve the information flow while reducing the spatial dimension.",
    "After the sixth convolutional layer, the spatial information is discarded, and a fully-connected layer is added to combine the information.",
    "Finally, two parallel layers with the same number of units as the latent-space dimension are used to output the mean and variance of the latent statistical distributions."
  ]
}